# IBM Cloud Credentials
# Get these from your IBM Cloud account at https://cloud.ibm.com
# NOTE: Only required if USE_OFFLINE_MODEL = False in src/config.py

# IBM Cloud API Key (from IBM Cloud IAM)
# Navigate to: Manage > Access (IAM) > API keys
IBM_API_KEY=your_ibm_cloud_api_key_here

# Watson ML Deployment ID
# Found in: Watson Studio > Deployments > Your Deployment > Deployment ID
DEPLOYMENT_ID=your_deployment_id_here

# IBM Cloud Region (where your ML model is deployed)
# Options: us-south, eu-gb, eu-de, jp-tok, au-syd, etc.
IBM_REGION=us-south

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env in the same directory
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual IBM Cloud credentials
# 3. Never commit the .env file to version control (already in .gitignore)
#
# OFFLINE MODE:
# If you want to use the offline XGBoost model instead of IBM Cloud:
# 1. Set USE_OFFLINE_MODEL = True in src/config.py
# 2. Run: python -m models.train_xgboost (to train the model first)
# 3. No IBM Cloud credentials needed!